                        <note>–</note>
                     </state>
                     <bibl>Ibn al-Najjār,al-Durra, 344</bibl>
                     <state type="addl-Descr">
                        <note>–<ref type="note" corresp="#Vol-4-A_F-ftn53"/>P:Arab. Pen.</note>
                     </state>
                     <floruit>385-420 CE<ref type="note" corresp="#Vol-4-A_F-ftn54"/>
                     </floruit>
                     <note xml:id="Vol-4-A_F-ftn52" n="2"> In Arabic – من بني زريق. On this tribe see Lecker (1995), MJP, 2, 9, 50, 57, 126.</note>
                     <note xml:id="Vol-4-A_F-ftn53" n="3"> Described in the text as من اليهود (of the Jews), see Introduction 6.1.</note>
                     <note xml:id="Vol-4-A_F-ftn54" n="4"> She is a contemporary of Abū Karīb (1) Tibān (1) Asʿad (1).  These are the dates of his reign, see Introduction 8.3.1.</note>
                  </person>
               </listPerson>
            </ab>
            <ab type="name" n="Qāmī-قامي">
               <ref type="note" corresp="#Vol-4-A_F-ftn55"/>
