                     </state>
                     <floruit>Pre-7thC CE<ref type="note" corresp="#Vol-4-A_F-ftn64"/>
                     </floruit>
                     <note xml:id="Vol-4-A_F-ftn61" n="2"> The names on the incantation bowls are in Jewish characters, see Introduction 5.2.1.</note>
                     <note xml:id="Vol-4-A_F-ftn62" n="3"> She writes at the end of the text: שמי קלימא בת יותא. The editor commented: “implies that the ‘client’ was the scribe.”</note>
                     <note xml:id="Vol-4-A_F-ftn63" n="4"> The authors of the Aramaic incantation bowls were Jewish, but there is no reason to suppose that all their clients were, see Introduction 6.7. </note>
